Package oogasalad.editor.controller

Class EditorPrefabManager

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.editor.controller.EditorPrefabManager
public class EditorPrefabManager extends Object
Manages the creation, saving, and loading of prefabs (Blueprints) to/from XML files.

    • EditorPrefabManager

      public EditorPrefabManager(EditorDataAPI editorDataAPI, EditorListenerNotifier notifier)
      Constructs an EditorPrefabManager.
      Parameters:
      editorDataAPI - The data API to access game directory path.
      notifier - The notifier to signal prefab changes and errors.

  • Method Details

    • saveAsPrefab

      public void saveAsPrefab(EditorObject objectToSave)
      Creates a prefab (BlueprintData) from an existing EditorObject and saves it to the prefabs XML file in the current game directory. Handles loading existing prefabs, checking for duplicates, assigning a new ID, and saving the updated list.
      Parameters:
      objectToSave - The EditorObject to convert and save as a prefab.

    • getPrefabFilePath

      private String getPrefabFilePath()
      Retrieves the full path to the prefab XML file within the current game directory.
      Returns:
      The absolute path string, or null if the game directory is not set.

    • loadPrefabsFromFile

      public Map<Integer,BlueprintData> loadPrefabsFromFile(File prefabFile)
      Loads prefab definitions (BlueprintData) from the specified XML file.
      Parameters:
      prefabFile - The File object representing the prefabs XML.
      Returns:
      A Map where keys are blueprint IDs and values are BlueprintData objects. Returns an empty map if the file doesn't exist or on parsing errors.
